      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">31.703</ph> Requirements.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1996e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2021e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            Contracts which refer to this <xref href="Subpart_31.7.dita#FAR_Subpart_31_7"
                        base="i1084365"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpartÂ  31.7</xref> for determining allowable costs shall be deemed to refer to, and shall have the allowability of costs determined by the contracting officer in accordance with, the OMB Uniform Guidance at <ph outputclass="CFR" class="- topic/ph ">2 CFR part 200</ph>, subpart E and appendix IV in effect on the date of the contract.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2021e21">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Agencies are not expected to place additional restrictions on individual items of cost. However, under 
                     <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3744&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3744</xref>
                     
                   and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section4304&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">41 U.S.C.4304</xref>, the costs cited in <xref href="31.603.dita#FAR_31_603"
                        base="i1084409"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">31.603</xref>(b) are unallowable.</p>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2021e34"/>
            </li>
         </ol>
